Boot Logs

dmesg (the traditional utility used for viewing the kernel ring buffer)
journalctl -k (systemd utility to view the kernel ring buffer within the systemd journal)

GRUB Shell

grub (entering into grub shell)
help (help with commands)
find (search for a file)
quit (exit grub shell)

GRUB 2

grub2-editenv list (view the deafult boot entry for the grub config file)
grub2-mkconfig (creates/configs config file)
update-grub
